event: Mary J Blige x Pepsi present Strength of a Woman Festival
briefdescription:
Mary J Blige x Pepsi present Strength of a Woman Festival 2024
The 2nd Annual Strength of a Woman festival featured two nights of packed line-ups and complete production solutions by Music Matters.
disclaimer:
Production included lighting, audio, video, staging, and rigging. The stage design was fully customized and featured over 900 LED panels.

Acts included Mary J Blige, Ciara, Jeezy, Lauryn Hill, Method Man, Busta Rhymes, Summer Walker and more
description:
Mary J. Blige brought her Strength of a Woman Festival to Atlanta that included a full line-up of artists at State Farm Arena. Music Matters provided all audio, lighting, and video for the show that included performances and appearances from MJB, Chaka Khan, Method Man, Usher, City Girls, and Ella Mai.

Arena shows offer a unique set of challenges for production including a same day load-in and load-out schedule for the crew. For this show, the lighting rig was also a custom design and different from your standard arena rig.

briefdescription: Music Matters Productions (MMP) collaborated with Winter Films to provide production support for a March Madness commercial shoot in Atlanta, commissioned by ESPN. The project involved a fast-paced timeline with a collaborative design process to achieve the desired look and feel. With only a basic rendering provided by the client, MMP’s team worked closely with Winter Films to translate the vision into reality.
disclaimer: The project timeline was condensed, requiring one day for setup and one day for shooting in the studio. Despite the tight schedule, MMP delivered exceptional results, showcasing their expertise in audio, lighting, reflective staging, and video production. The team’s adaptability and efficiency ensured that they met the client’s tight deadline without compromising on quality.
